types.name: DataSourceDTO
types.description:
DataSourceDTO is used to uniquely identify a DataSource. DataSourceDTO object holds all
 information that describe a data source. For example, the temp and the humidity sensors are two
 datasources that exist in a Yanzi Climate device. It contains a DataSource object, the SI Unit it
 is measured with and the time of generation.

types.name: DataTransformation
types.description: Contains sample translation information. Used in TimeSerieSelection to request a transformed stream.

types.name: DeviceAcceptState
types.description:
The DeviceAcceptState is used to describe physical things that are not currently managed by our
 system and only limited information about them may be available. The accept state is also used to
 show more detailed authentication status for things we don't trust.

types.name: DeviceUpState
types.description: Contains all the states a device may be in to.

types.name: EventDTO
types.description:
EventDTO object holds all information that describe an event. For example, an event occurs when a
 new device is accepted in a system. The type of the event is mentioned in the EventType property.
 It contains a UnitAddress object, the time the event occured and a list of DTO objects.

types.name: EventType
types.description:
Contains all different types of events that can occur in a system. These types are included in
 the EventDTO message that is pushed to all connected clients.

types.name: FactoryDefaultType
types.description: Used in FactoryDefault message to indicate the type of the device the message is referring to.

types.name: Float
types.description: The `Float` scalar type represents signed double-precision fractional values as specified by [IEEE 754](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_floating_point).

types.name: ID
types.description: The `ID` scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as `"4"`) or integer (such as `4`) input value will be accepted as an ID.

types.name: Int
types.description: The `Int` scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

types.name: KeyValueDTO
types.description: Contains a Pair type-value, where the value is a Long.

types.name: LevelState
types.description: Describes the level that an unit or asset is full at.

types.name: LifeCycleState

Contains all different states of a life cycle of a unit. It is included in the UnitDTO along with the rest of the

LocationAddress object is used to uniquely identify a location consisting of one or more sensors.
 It cointains the location id and the server id.

types.description:
LocationDTO object holds all information that describe a location. It contains a time of
 generation, a time of last modification, a LocationAddress object, a name, an account id, a
 gateway id and Yanzi Server id.

types.name: ProvisioningDTO
types.description:
ProvisioningDTO object holds all information that describe a the provisioning state of a unit.
 It contains the id of the sensor (normally the Hardware serial number EUI64-XXX), the locationId,
 the public key of the device, the DeployState indicating the device state in the system, the productType
 and optionally the properties and the position of the device. If existing it may also contain the virtualId and the
 planningId of the device.

fields.name: unit
fields.description: The unit created by this provisioning. Will return null unless the deployState == provisioned.

Get the location with the specific location id. If the id is not specified, then the system will pick the most
 appropriate location.

types.name: Range
types.description: The Range object is used to define a time period. It contains a start and an end point in time.

types.name: RealmDTO
types.description: Not available yet! - RealmDTO object the minimale information that describe a Yanzi Master Server.

types.name: ResponseCode
types.description:
Contains all different response codes that exist. Response codes are included in all responses
 that are being dispatched as a result of a request message, and indicate whether the result of
 the requested operation. The most common is "success", that indicates that everything when
 smoothly, however there are many cases that something may go wrong. Useful also for development
 purposes.

types.name: SampleAccelerometer
types.description: Sample that contains the information from an accelerometer sensor.

types.name: SampleAsset
types.description:
The SampleAsset object is used to represent a sample comming from an asset entity. It contains an
 AssetState and (optionally) a LevelState value.

types.name: SampleBattery
types.description: The SampleBattery contains the voltage measured in millivolts (mV) as a value and the corresponding percentage of battery left.

types.name: SampleBatteryPower
types.description: The SampleBatteryPower object contains all information about the status of the battery.

types.name: SampleBoolean
types.description: The SampleBoolean object is used to represent a sample of a binary source (true or false).

types.name: SampleBooleanCounter
types.description:
The SampleBooleanCounter object is samilar to the SampleBoolean one, but it also contains a counter
 value.

types.name: SampleCO2
types.description:
The SampleCO2 object is used to represent a sample generated from a CO2 sensor. The value is
 reported in ppm(eg. 567ppm of CO2).

types.name: SampleCommunicationStatistics
types.description:
The SampleCommunicationStatistics object contains statistics about the communication 
 of a certain unit.

types.name: SampleDTO
types.description:
The Sample class represents a single piece of data coming from a sensor. It is the superclass of
 the specific classes that describe specific data ({@link SampleBoolean}, {@link SampleLong},
 {@link SampleDouble},{@link SampleBooleanCounter}), {@link SampleString} and represent data used
 for temperature, humidity , motion etc. This class only contains the value of the time (long for
 msec) that the sample was captured.

types.name: SampleDistance
types.description:
The SampleDistance object is used to represent a sample containing a distance value. This value
 is measured in mm(eg. 1234mm).

types.name: SampleDouble
types.description: The SampleDouble object is used to represent a sample containing a double value (eg. 12.34).

types.name: SampleDraining
types.description:
The SampleDraining object represents the Draining State for a measurement. The value indicates the Total Instant
 Power drained in mW. The Draining state (draining/not draining) is calculated using the thresholds in the sample.

types.name: SampleElectricalEnergySimple
types.description:
The SampleElectricalEnergySimple object contains a sample generated from a general output device.
 It always contains the value of the totalEnergy consumed by the device expressed in mWs and the
 instant power expressed in W.
 It may also contain the voltage of the line expressed in mV, the current intensity expressed in mA,
 the total amount of apparent energy expressed in mWs and the total amount of time expressed in ms
 that the instant power has been above 25W.

types.name: SampleEndOfSlot
types.description:
The SampleEndOfSlot object is used to represent the last sample received during an slot
 (time interval) it contains a slotSize that defines that interval size and the mentioned sample.

types.name: SampleFootfall
types.description:
SampleFootfall contains information about the main counter of a Footfall camera.
 The main value (value) is the ingress counter and the sample also contains the egress counter. The devicesMissing / total is
 used in aggregations over multiple sensors in assets. A user may use that value to judge the accuracy of the value.

types.name: SampleForce
types.description: The SampleForce object is used to represent a sample containing force in milliNewtons (eg. 9800 mN).

types.name: SampleGyro
types.description: Sample that contains the information from a gyroscope sensor.

types.name: SampleHumidity
types.description:
The SampleHumidity ojbect is used to represent a sample containing humidity value in percentage (0-100).
 Optionally it can contain also a temperature value expressed in Kelvins.

types.name: SampleIlluminance
types.description:
The SampleIlluminance object is used to represent a sample containing illuminance in mlux (eg. 567000 mlux).
 If supported by the sensor element, it will also contain the colorTemperature in K (eg. 5725 K).

types.name: SampleImage
types.description:
SampleImageTime represents a sample which contain the time stamp of an image existing
 in the database.

types.name: SampleLamp
types.description:
The SampleLamp object contains a sample created from a Yanzi LED. It contains a value
 indicating the percentage of intensity of the lamp (0 off - 100 totally on) and
 a counter indicating how many times the lamp has been switched.

fields.name: timeLastDataSync
fields.description: Time of Last Data Synchronized

types.name: SampleLog
types.description: The SampleLog objects contains logging info from a device.

types.name: SampleLong
types.description: The SampleLong object is used to represent a sample that contains a long value.

types.name: SampleMotion
types.description:
Sample for describing the state of a Motion device. The value indicates the number of times that motion has
 been detected since the node last boot and increments for every motion. timeLastMotion indicates the Time
 of the last motion in ms since epoch.

types.name: SampleMotion2Lars
types.description:
Sample for describing the state of a Motion device. Every time motion is detected the motion
 counter is incremented one or more times.

types.name: SampleOnOff
types.description:
The SampleOnOff object represents the state of a source that can either be on (true) or off (false).
 It contains an optional toggle counter.

types.name: SampleOpenClosed
types.description:
The SampleOpenClosed object represents the state of a source that can either be open, closed or in an unknown state.
 It also contains the time of the last state change. It contains an optional open counter
 and an optional closed counter.

types.name: SampleParticulateMatter
types.description:
The SampleParticulateMatter object is used to represent a sample generated from a particulate matter sensor. There are 4 possible samples points.

Note! Normally not every value is present in the sample.

All the sample points are in micrograms/m^3.

The pm10 represent sample for particles with a size less than 1.0 micrometer The pm25 represent sample for particles with a size less than 2.5 micrometer The pm40 represent sample for particles with a size less than 4.0 micrometer The pm100 represent sample for particles with a size less than 10.0 micrometer

types.name: SamplePeopleCount
types.description:
Sample for describing the number of people an unit. The number in represent how many people is in an
 area or something similar.

types.name: SamplePercentage
types.description: The SamplePercentage object is used to represent a sample containing a percentage.

types.name: SamplePosition
types.description: The SamplePosition object is used to represent a sample containing a position of an entity.

types.name: SamplePressure
types.description: The SamplePressure object is used to represent a sample containing pressure in Pa (eg. 101300 Pa).

types.name: SamplePulseBand
types.description: Sample that contains the information from a pulse band.

types.name: SampleRefillList
types.description: The SampleRefillList is deprecated.

types.name: SampleSiteOnlineStatus
types.description: The sample online status contains aggregated information on site connectivity.

types.name: SampleSoundPressureLevel
types.description:
The SampleSoundPressureLevel object is used to represent a sample containing sound pressure in mBA (milli Bell A-rated).
 The main value is the average sound pressure level during the measured inteval.
 It also contains the min and the max value observed during that interval and the corresponding SampleStatus that
 will indicate if measured values are outside the limits.

types.name: SampleStack
types.description: Contains the quantity of elements in a stack.

types.name: SampleStatus
types.description:
SampleStatus gives extra information about the sampleValue. For example, if the measure is 
 only a lower threshold instead of an actual value when greaterThan SampleStatus is set.

types.name: SampleString
types.description: The SampleString object is used to represent a sample that contains a value that is a string.

types.name: SampleTemp
types.description: SampleTemp object is used to represent a sample containing temperature value.

types.name: SampleUpState
types.description: Sample used to indicate the UpState of a device. Eg. connected/disconnected

types.name: SampleUtilization
types.description:
The SampleUtilization object contains utilization information of an asset.
 It indicates the number of child assets in free, occupied or other state (missingInput, unknown, etc.)

types.name: SampleVOC
types.description:
The SampleVOC object is used to represent a sample generated from a Volatile Organic
 Compound sensor. The value is reported in ppb(eg. 122 parts per billion).

types.name: SampleVOCIndex
types.description: For some sensor getEquivalentTvoc value can also be available. It is defined in ppm.

types.name: SampleWeight
types.description:
SampleWeight object is used to represent a sample containing weight value. The value it
 contains is expressed in kilograms (kg).

types.name: ServiceDetailsDTO
types.description: Contains information regarding the service provided.

types.name: ShrekDTO
types.description: ShrekDTO object holds information about a ShrekInstance.

types.name: SlotDTO
types.description:
The object contains the information about sensor values over a time period.
 The time period is defined by the SlotSize.
 It contains information about the min, max, sum (called aggregateValue) and the number of samples which the sum is based on over the time period.
 The aggregateValue is the sum of the sample values.
 The maxValueTime is the time of the sample containing the max value.
 the minValueTime is the time of the sample containing the min value.

types.name: SlotSize
types.description: This is the definition of slot size. It specifies the time span of a slot.

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

types.name: SubscriptionType
types.description: Contains all possible types of subscriptions someone can request to subscribe to.

types.name: SystemUserAcl
types.description: Contains all possible access levels a user can have on a per account basis.

types.name: UnitAcl
types.description: Contains all possible access levels a user can have on a per unit basis.

types.name: UnitAddress
types.description:
UnitAddress object is used to identify a unique unit. It contains a did, a locationId and a
 serverDid.

types.name: UnitAlarmSetValues
types.description: UnitAlarmSetValues. States which can be set to an alarm.

types.name: UnitDTO
types.description:
UnitDTO object holds all information that describe a Yanzi unit. For example, the temp and the
 humidity sensors are two units that exist in a Yanzi Climate device. It contains a DataSource
 object, the SI Unit it is measured with and the time of generation.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByURL`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

args.name: reason
args.description: Explains why this element was deprecated, usually also including a suggestion for how to access supported similar data. Formatted using the Markdown syntax, as specified by [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/).

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: specifiedBy
directives.description: Exposes a URL that specifies the behavior of this scalar.

args.name: url
args.description: The URL that specifies the behavior of this scalar.
